messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- Full HTTP request path:
  - /api/paste

- All HTTP methods acceptable:
  - false

- HEAD:

- POST:
  - true

- OPTIONS:
  - false

- TRACE:
  - false

- GET:
  - false

- PUT:
  - false

- DELETE:
  - false

- PATCH:
  - false

Explanation:
- The controller class has @RequestMapping("/api/paste") at class level. The method postNewCodePasteWith is annotated with @PostMapping with no path, so it maps to POST requests to the class-level path: /api/paste.
- There is an explicit POST mapping for /api/paste, so POST = true.
- There are no explicit mappings in the code for HEAD, OPTIONS, TRACE, GET, PUT, DELETE, or PATCH at the exact path /api/paste. (The code contains GET mappings for /api/paste/{paste_id} and /api/paste/public and a DELETE mapping for /api/paste/{paste_id}, but those are different paths and do not make /api/paste itself available for those HTTP methods.)
- Per your instruction, I did not assume automatic framework behavior (for example, Spring can implicitly handle HEAD or OPTIONS in some cases). The determinations above are strictly based on explicit annotations present in the source code.
